description: The National Tribal Healthy Homes Assessment, Training & Technical Assistance Support Center is a program of Montana State University Extension, Housing and Environmental Health Program, funded by the U.S. Department of Housing and Urban Development. The center integrates elements of the existing National Center for Healthy Housing and the Usda/Hud Healthy Homes Partnership program to help tribal communities assess homes for common indoor health hazards such as mold and moisture, carbon monoxide, household chemicals, unsafe drinking water, lead, asbestos, pesticides, radon, dust and dust mites, allergens, asthma triggers, and fire and safety hazards and septic systems. description: Kentucky River Coal Corporation (Krcc) is a land holding company that was established nearly a century ago by John C. C. Mayo and W. S. Dudley.
